name: Tea Point
address: Jl. Untung Surapati No.108, Padang Kerta, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1:
The place has no aircond. Surprisingly, it wasn‚Äôt hot due to the huge ceiling fans!
Their foods were GREAT!
Must try their Nasi Kulit (Chicken skin rice) and thank me later.
Food presentation was aesthetic too.
Their coffee was nice as well!
review 2: The service is excellent, one of the waitress help out to took some picture for me and my friends. She was so friendly. The pizza was amazing, you should try the chicken mushroom one. Will come back for sure!
review 3: Tea Point definitely had a good vibe in it. They have big windows in the 2nd floor, you can clearly see green soothing view outside. I came in rainy day, it was splendid afternoon..the rain, good choice of Playlist and warm tea. To sum it up, tea pot is a place with a nice vibe to chat on with friends or to do your work. The food is okay for me. The minus is they use plastic spoon and plastic glass even for dining in.
review 4:
Love the vibe & food  ‚ù§Ô∏è
Good place to spend time with couple and friends
review 5:
went there just for drinks. Tea was gernerous in a pot and delicious, coffee also good.

Upstairs seating offers volcano views when the weather is good.

The staff is very sweet - it started raining heavily and they fetched our helmets from the parking so they would stay dry.

name: TOPAZ Kitchen
address: Jl. Untung Surapati No.162, Padang Kerta, kabupaten, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1: The best Pasta and Caesar Salad in Bali. Cold drinks & seriously great food. Yes its a cafe so no airs and graces but an absolutely delicious menu. Pricing that will not break the bank either. Great staff and hosts also to ensure you enjoy.
review 2:
We really enjoyed the food there. Indeed, the place was very pleasant and clean. The waitress was also super nice and polite with us. If we ever come again in this area of Bali, for sure we'll repeat!

Value for money is very good!
review 3: This restaurant is a gem. The food is great, the venue is clean and nice, the  service was perfect and the  price is affordable (maybe a bit noisy as the main road is nearby but it‚Äôs common in Indonesia). I would definitely recommend and I will go again for sur. I tried the Carbonara pasta and the crumble for dessert ü§åüèº
review 4: Cozy place, beef burger, chicken quesadillas, pizza, and apple pie was great, good services tho. Definitely will come back again :)
review 5: Must try! So happy we found this place in Amlapura a couple of days ago and eating here already the 2nd day. They also deliver to Jasri for a small fee. Really nice place, no cats (which is great because I am allergic), yammie Pizza, Pasta, Quesadillas and smoothies. Putu and her husband do an amazing job!

name: Babi Guling Gusti Ayu
address: Padang Kerta, Karangasem, Karangasem Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Really delicious Babi Guling, but watch the chilli here it is spicy!
review 2: This place rocks! The babi guling is to die for! Skin is so crispy and the servings are really generous. Try the local food, it's better than any tourist restaurant in Amed. You'll thank me!
review 3: Amazing babi guling and chargrilled skewers! Would be back every day if it wasn't so far from our accommodation. Be sure to check this place out on the way back from Heaven's Gate!

name: Kedai d'Jakarta Rooftop
address: Jl. Serma Natih Lingkungan kertasari No.6, Padang Kerta, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80813, Indonesia
review 1: Really nice place to eat. We loved the rooftop, the staff is really nice and the vibes were good. The food is really affordable and delicious! We would definitely recommend and come back another time.
review 2: Super delicious food, loved the honey grilled chicken! Amazing staff, they are very friendly and speak English well. The rooftop is also amazing and has a great atmosphere.
review 3:
The best warung in town! Owned and served by an experienced chef. He is a good, kind, and friendly person.
You'll get awesome food with fine portions and cheap prices.

One word to describe this warung: fantastic!
review 4: Very nice service. The staff over here gives you very good recommendations and explains the food in a detailed way. Food itself was really nice we enjoyed the chicken dumplings and the jackarta‚Äôs noodles. Definitely reccomended
review 5: Nice place, the service is good. I bought Mie Pangsit Special (if i'm not mistaken), it has noodle, sweet diced chicken and mushrooms, dumplings and meatballs. The noodles was light, easy to eat. Sweet chicken and mushrooms was good companion to complement savory broth and noodles. The dumplings is my favorite, must try. The meatballs surprised me, in general meatball's taste is in the savory side, but this one i can taste slightly sweet. I like it.

She told me they use powder (ABC coffee or stuff like that i suppose). It went straight to the garbage. Cannot believe they charge like 20k for some powder coffee, not even real beans.
review 2: I have visited some nau here and so far I like this one. Good hospitality, nice place to hang out, and clean.
review 3: A nice small coffee place.  Has wifi and good for hanging out
